    <h4>Description:</h4>
    <p>Rajma Chawal is a classic North Indian comfort food made with red kidney beans cooked in a spicy onion-tomato gravy and served with steamed basmati rice.</p>

    <h4>Prep Time:</h4>
    <p>‚è±Ô∏è <strong>45 minutes</strong></p>

    <h4>Ingredients:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>1 cup rajma (kidney beans)</li>
        <li>2 cups water for soaking</li>
        <li>2 medium onions (finely chopped)</li>
        <li>2 tomatoes (pureed)</li>
        <li>1 tsp ginger-garlic paste</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp turmeric powder</li>
        <li>1 tsp red chili powder</li>
        <li>1 tsp garam masala</li>
        <li>Salt to taste</li>
        <li>2 tbsp oil or ghee</li>
        <li>Fresh coriander leaves for garnish</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Instructions:</h4>
    <ol>
        <li>Soak rajma overnight or for at least 8 hours. Drain and rinse.</li>
        <li>Pressure cook rajma with fresh water and a little salt for 4‚Äì5 whistles or until soft.</li>
        <li>Heat oil in a pan, saut√© onions until golden brown.</li>
        <li>Add ginger-garlic paste and cook for 2 minutes.</li>
        <li>Add tomato puree, turmeric, red chili powder, and cook until oil separates.</li>
        <li>Add boiled rajma and a little water. Simmer for 15 minutes.</li>
        <li>Add garam masala and cook for another 5 minutes.</li>
        <li>Garnish with coriander leaves and serve hot with steamed rice.</li>
    </ol>
